entries.description: A Packers and Bears fan duked it out at their favorite teams' Dec. 4 matchup at Soldier Field. The Bears fan got the win in the stands, but the Packers won again on the field.

entries.title: Packers and Bears fans fight in upper deck of Soldier Field, Green Bay supporter pushed down stairs
entries.description: A Packers and Bears fan got into a fight in the stands in a battle that led to the Green Bay supporter getting pushed down the stairs at Soldier Field.

entries.title: Shannon Sharpe roasts Deion Sanders over amputated toes: 'I thought you was magic'
entries.description: Deion Sanders had two of his toes amputated last year after complications from surgery. When Shannon Sharpe visited Coach Prime, he had to crack some jokes.

entries.title: Boris Becker claims inmate tried to kill him while in prison: 'I was shaking so bad'
entries.description: German tennis legend Boris Becker said he was "shaking so bad" when an inmate tried to sexually assault him, while claiming another tried to kill him while he served 8 months in prison.

entries.title: Tucker presses Texas governor on state's actions to secure border while Biden fails to
entries.description: Texas Gov. Greg Abbott joined Tucker Carlson on "Tucker Carlson Tonight" to debate the veracity with which his National Guard is trying to secure the border.

entries.title: Iran's top prosecutor, key military figures sanctioned by Treasury over protest crackdowns
entries.description: The Department of Treasury announced sanctions on Wednesday against Iran's Prosecutor General and top military officials over the country's crackdown on protests.

entries.title: Charlbi Dean cause of death confirmed after sudden passing at 32: coroner
entries.description: Actress and model Charlbi Dean Kriek died of bacterial sepsis in August, according to the New York City coroner. Her death at age 32 was ruled an accident.

entries.title: TUCKER CARLSON: Zelenskyy's visit represented 'bipartisan masochism'
entries.description: Fox News host Tucker Carlson reacted to Ukraine President Volodymyr Zelenskyy's address to Congress on 'Tucker Carlson Tonight.'

entries.title: Taiwanese officials say 39 Chinese military aircrafts, 3 ships, entered area close to island
entries.description: Taiwanese officials say that 39 Chinese military aircraft and three vessels traveled close to the island on Thursday morning as tensions escalate between the two countries.

entries.title: Idaho murders: Moscow police chief says quadruple murder case 'is not going cold'
entries.description: Moscow Police Department Chief James Fry said that the investigation surrounding the murders of four University of Idaho students "is not going cold."

entries.title: Pope Francis orders Vatican Museums to return Parthenon marble sculptures to Greece
entries.description: The three fragments, held by the Vatican since the 19th century, consist of a head of a boy, a bearded male head, and a part of a horse's head.

entries.title: Eagles lead the way with 8 Pro Bowlers as rosters announced
entries.description: The 13-1 Philadelphia Eagles will have an NFL-high eight representatives at the Pro Bowl, with QB Jalen Hurts and WR A.J. Brown each tabbed as starters.

entries.title: Washington DC police impersonator on the loose after shooting 2 people, cops say
entries.description: Washington D.C. police are looking for a gunman they say impersonated an officer before shooting two people.

entries.title: Russia warns US military aid to Ukraine will escalate conflict as Zelenskyy addresses Congress
entries.description: Russia warned Wednesday that the United States' continued support of Ukraine through military aid would only worsen the 10-month conflict.

entries.title: Titans' Ryan Tannehill 'very likely' out for the rest of the season; rookie QB Malik Willis to start: report
entries.description: According to Titans reporter Paul Kuharsky, the veteran quarterback is "very likely" done for the season because the ankle injury he suffered may require surgery.

entries.title: Book shows alleged Biden-Harris divide surfaced earlier than previous president-VP rifts, some critics say
entries.description: President Joe Biden and Vice President Kamala Harris' relationship in the administration was part of the subject of a new book by author Chris Whipple.

entries.title: Zelenskyy makes direct appeal to GOP critics, arguing no country is safe if Ukraine falters
entries.description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy made a direct appeal to GOP critics, arguing that no country would be safe if Ukraine failed to combat Russia's aggression.

entries.title: Incoming Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu says he has formed new coalition government
entries.description: Benjamin Netanyahu said Wednesday evening that he has formed a new government after his Likud Party and allies won a majority during last month's elections.

entries.title: New York City alleged subway shooter to plead guilty to shooting 10 people in April: prosecutors
entries.description: The man who allegedly opened fire in a New York City subway car in April 2022 is expected to plead guilty to charges connected with committing a terrorist attack.

entries.title: Kansas man convicted of performing illegal autopsies gets additional jail time
entries.description: A Kansas man will serve another year in prison in connection with an illegal autopsy scheme, authorities said.

entries.title: Washington Post report blasted for stating 'the obvious' about benefits of exercise on COVID 2 years later
entries.description: A Washington Post column acknowledging the benefits of exercise to avoid fatal COVID was blasted on Twitter for taking years to admit what was 'obvious' to most of the public.

entries.title: JESSE WATTERS: Congress crafted a dirty system that's bankrupting America
entries.description: Fox News host Jesse Watters rips Congress' $1.7 trillion omnibus spending bill and calls out lawmakers for hurrying the process on "Jesse Watters Primetime."

entries.title: Former Washington DC police officers found guilty in death of man in 2020 moped chase
entries.description: Two former Washington D.C., police officers were found guilty in relation to the death of a moped rider during a police chase

entries.title: Rob Gronkowski fires off cryptic tweet that sends NFL fans into frenzy
entries.description: Could Rob Gronkowski be itching to return to the NFL again? His cryptic tweet Wednesday night said he was "kinda bored," which sent NFL fans into a frenzy.

entries.title: Former fentanyl addict discusses addiction, recovery: 'These drugs will sink their claws into you'
entries.description: A former fentanyl addict tells his story of addiction and his long road to recovery. Liam O'Brien found a dealer on Craig's List and nearly overdosed the first time he tried it.

entries.title: 'Bomb cyclone' to impact holiday travel with blizzards, cold temps across the nation
entries.description: A Christmas blizzard is expected to turn into a bomb cyclone this week, snarling highway and airport traffic across much of the U.S. with freezing temps, high winds and snow.

entries.title: Texas federal judge rules against HHS program allowing teens confidential birth control
entries.description: A Texas district judge ruled that Title X, a federal program that provides free, confidential contraception to anyone violates parents' rights and state and federal law.

entries.title: Texas FedEx driver accused of murdering 7-year-old girl faces unrelated sexual assault of a child charges
entries.description: Tanner Horner, a 31-year-old man jailed for allegedly murdering a 7-year-old girl three weeks ago, was charged with sexual assault of a child in a separate case this week.

entries.title: Kate Moss models electric pink hair reminiscent of iconic '90s makeover for new Marc Jacobs campaign
entries.description: Kate Moss revived an iconic style from the nineties with an incredible transformation into bold pink hair for her latest fashion campaign with Marc Jacob.

entries.title: New York City police say 12-year-old boy robbed at gunpoint
entries.description: New York City Police say that a 12-year-old boy was robbed at gunpoint last Thursday night, and had his sweatshirt and backpack taken in the incident.

entries.title: Keith Olbermann admonishes Democrats to fight back: 'When they go low, we get baseball bats'
entries.description: Far-left commentator Keith Olbermann called for Democrats to “get baseball bats” in response to Republicans retaking the House during a podcast on Wednesday.

entries.title: Clemson's Dabo Swinney gives his unique take on NIL: 'We built this program in God's name, image and likeness'
entries.description: NIL allows collegiate athletes to profit off of their name, image and likeness. It also lets them transfer without restrictions. The program has made schools reimagine recruiting.

entries.title: Austin city department's 'mommy killing Santa Claus' Christmas driving safety tweets raise concerns
entries.description: The City of Austin, Texas is running a series of promotional tweets during the holiday season to raise awareness of the dangers of driving with distractions.

entries.title: NASA’s Mars rover deposits first sample on Red Planet for possible return to earth
entries.description: NASA's Mars rover deposited the first sample of rocks on the Red Planet's surface so that they could eventually return to Earth for further analysis.

entries.title: Mike Pence seen as ‘p---y’ for not supporting indictment of Trump: MSNBC guest
entries.description: MSNBC regular Kurt Andersen slammed former Vice President Mike Pence as a 'p---y" and a "wimp" for not supporting the indictment of former President Donald Trump.
